<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2126/316.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Furniss</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-11-23"><hi rend="italic">November 23,
                                    1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Root acknowledges his telegram of November 21, and directs Mr.
                            Furniss to convey to the Haitian Government the usual notice that
                            blockade must be proclaimed and maintained by an adequate force in order
                            to be respected.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>